4
00:00:25,710 --> 00:00:28,630
<b>美国派拉蒙电影公司</b> 出 品

5
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:33,050
<b>\h协助出品</b> 美国孩之宝

6
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:49,950
我们曾经是一群爱好和平的智能化机械种族
We were once a peaceful race of intelligent, mechanical beings.

7
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:53,000
但后来爆发了战争
But then came the war

8
00:00:53,090 --> 00:00:56,630
一方是汽车人 为自由而战
between the Autobots, who fought for freedom

9
00:00:56,720 --> 00:01:00,210
另一方则是霸天虎 却妄图称霸
and the Decepticons, who dreamt of tyranny.

10
00:01:03,810 --> 00:01:06,180
敌强我弱 敌众我寡
Overmatched and outnumbered,

11
00:01:06,270 --> 00:01:08,930
我们必败无疑
our defeat was all but certain.

12
00:01:22,740 --> 00:01:25,240
但就在战争临近尾声之时
But in the war's final days,

13
00:01:25,330 --> 00:01:28,120
一艘汽车人飞船冲出了纷飞的战火
one Autobot ship escaped the battle.

14
00:01:28,210 --> 00:01:30,820
飞船上载着一批秘密货物
It was carrying a secret cargo,

15
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:33,750
它本可以改变我们母星的命运
which would have changed our planet's fate.

16
00:01:44,850 --> 00:01:46,390
那是最后的拼死一搏
A desperate mission.

17
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:49,100
承载着我们最后的希望
Our final hope.

18
00:02:02,030 --> 00:02:04,490
而这希望也破灭了
A hope that vanished.

19
00:02:10,620 --> 00:02:13,030
<b>VLA电波天文台新墨西哥州 1961年</b>

20
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:15,090
一个在那里 一个在这里
One up there. One over there.

21
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:17,300
还有一个在这里
And one more down there.

22
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:24,590
有什么收获？
What you got?

23
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,730
探测到撞击
Impact detected.

24
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:44,410
确认发生撞击 接触时间为20:50
We have impact confirmed. Contact at 2250 GMT.

25
00:02:42,490 --> 00:02:45,150
<b>国家宇航局局长 兰利 弗吉尼亚州</b>

26
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:45,900
什么？
What?

27
00:02:47,410 --> 00:02:49,570
马上给我接通国防部长
Get me SecDef on the phone right away.

28
00:02:49,830 --> 00:02:51,950
<b>紧急</b> 观测到深空轨迹 监测到月面撞击

29
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,940
<b>国家安全指挥部 五角大楼</b>

30
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,090
麦克·纳马拉部长 总统先生在等您
Mr. McNamara, the President is expecting you.

31
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:10,720
让鲍比进来
Get Bobby in here.

32
00:03:10,810 --> 00:03:13,270
总统先生 最高机密
Mr. President, designation, top secret.

33
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,520
有一艘不明飞行物在在月球上坠落
We believe a UFO has crashed into the Moon.

34
00:03:15,610 --> 00:03:17,770
苏联人应该也在调查此事
We think the Russians are onto it as well.

35
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:20,350
命令航天局要动用一切力量
Well, then you tell NASA to move heaven and earth.

36
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:21,650
我们得登上月球
We need to get to the moon.

37
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:23,700
我们得实现一次载人探月行动
We're going to attempt a manned mission.

38
00:03:23,780 --> 00:03:25,690
航天局认为这得花上5年
NASA said it would take five years.

39
00:03:25,780 --> 00:03:27,780
必须抢在苏联人之前登月
You get there before the Russians.

40
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,360
我相信我国人民能够齐聚一心全力以赴
I believe that this nation should commit itself

41
00:03:31,830 --> 00:03:33,240
达成这个目标
to achieving the goal

42
00:03:34,210 --> 00:03:35,700
在这个十年结束前
before this decade is out

43
00:03:36,340 --> 00:03:39,950
人类将登陆到月球并且安全返回地球
of landing a man on the moon and returning him safely to the Earth.

44
00:03:40,050 --> 00:03:42,160
启动发射程序
Ignition sequence start.

45
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:47,720
（8年后 1969年7月16日） 五 四 三 二 一
Five, four, three, two, one.

46
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:46,800
<b>8年后 1969年7月16日</b>

47
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:49,390
全部引擎工作正常
All engines running.

48
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:51,840
发射 已经发射
Liftoff. We have a liftoff.

49
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:55,640
时间是9点32分 阿波罗11号发射升空
Thirty-two minutes past the hour. Liftoff on Apollo 11.

50
00:03:56,860 --> 00:04:00,900
尼尔·阿姆斯特朗报告阿波罗11号飞行轨道正确
Neil Armstrong reporting Apollo 11 on proper heading.

51
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:03,400
阿波罗11号开始了旅程
Apollo 11 is on the way,

52
00:04:03,490 --> 00:04:04,520
乘着强焰之柱
riding that pillar of flame

53
00:04:04,610 --> 00:04:09,230
由土星5号火箭喷射而出 奔向了25万英哩之外
from the Saturn V out there, 250,000 miles away,

54
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:11,190
月球正在那里静候着
where the moon is waiting

55
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:13,400
人类的首次造访
for man 's first arrival.

56
00:04:16,460 --> 00:04:18,250
这里是休斯顿 现在准备降落 完毕
Houston, you're a go for landing. Over.

57
00:04:19,340 --> 00:04:22,800
40英尺 下降2.5英尺 扬起了一些灰尘
Forty feet, down two and a half. Picking up some dust.

58
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:27,010
30英尺 下降2.5英尺 模糊的影子
Thirty feet, two and a half down. Faint shadow.

59
00:04:27,510 --> 00:04:28,880
宇航通讯员 飞行
Capcom, flight.

60
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,930
向前4英尺 向右漂移一点点
Four forward. Drifting to the right a little.

61
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,260
下降0.5英尺
Down a half.

62
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,850
轻轻降落
Contact light.

63
00:04:38,110 --> 00:04:39,310
好了 关闭引擎
Okay, engine stop.

64
00:04:41,190 --> 00:04:42,270
休斯顿
Houston,

65
00:04:42,530 --> 00:04:44,810
这里是静海基地
Tranquility Base here.

66
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:46,360
小鹰号登月舱已经着陆
The Eagle has landed.

67
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:49,150
收到着陆讯号 小鹰号
We copy you down, Eagle.

68
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,030
你们把大家的脸都快憋青了
You got a bunch of guys about to turn blue.

69
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,370
总算能松口气了
We're breathing again.

70
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:55,770
<b>最高机密</b>

71
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:58,780
大约有4亿人正在观看今日的直播
Perhaps 400 million persons are watching this broadcast today

72
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:03,000
见证这一时代最伟大的成就…
of the greatest event in our time

73
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,290
这也是铭载史册的一大壮举
and one of the great events of all recorded history.

74
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:07,880
我下到了梯子的底部
I'm at the foot of the ladder.

75
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:11,550
好的 现在走下了登月舱
Okay, I'm gonna step off the LEM now.

76
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:16,220
这是我个人的一小步…
That's one small step for man,

77
00:05:17,230 --> 00:05:20,060
但却是人类的一大步
one giant leap for mankind.

78
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:23,310
- 准备好了没？ - 好了 长官
- Are we good? - Yes, sir.

79
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:26,310
转到1092非正式频道…
Unofficial time on the first step, 109....

80
00:05:32,370 --> 00:05:35,330
阿波罗11号 这里是休斯顿 完毕
Apollo 11? This is Houston, over.

81
00:05:35,660 --> 00:05:38,000
小鹰号 我们遇到了讯号干扰
Eagle, we're getting a signal interference.

82
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:38,910
你们听到了吗？
Do you copy?

83
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,700
刚刚得到证实
We now have had confirmation

84
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,910
暂时出现中断
of loss of signal

85
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:45,830
与阿波罗11号的联系
from the Apollo 11.

86
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:49,840
阿波罗11号此刻正在月球的背面
The Apollo 11 is, at the moment, on the far side of the moon.

87
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:57,340
尼尔 你正在月球的背面
Neil, you are dark on the rock.

88
00:05:57,770 --> 00:05:59,350
开始执行任务
Mission is a go.

89
00:06:00,110 --> 00:06:01,850
你们有21分钟
We have 21 minutes.

90
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:25,600
阿波罗11号 你们还有13分45秒…
The Apollo 11, We have 13 minutes and 45 seconds.

91
00:06:45,690 --> 00:06:46,730
我的天啊
My God.

92
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:49,900
好像是张巨大的金属面孔
It's some sort of giant metal face.

93
00:06:49,990 --> 00:06:51,440
天啊…
Jesus.

94
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:59,110
控制中心 我们进入飞船了
Control, we are inside the ship.

95
00:07:03,170 --> 00:07:05,250
船体受损严重
Extensive damage.

96
00:07:05,340 --> 00:07:07,950
难以对飞船进行全面检查
Way too big to check the entire ship.

97
00:07:13,470 --> 00:07:16,130
这里一片死寂 休斯顿
Everything's dead in here, Houston.

98
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:18,050
没有任何生命迹象
No signs of life anywhere.

99
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:22,010
这些东西巨大无比
These things are massive.

100
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:26,600
收到 你们的氧气还能维持7分钟
We copy. You've got seven minutes on your oxygen.

101
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:29,060
宇宙中并不只有我们 对吗？
We are not alone after all, are we?

102
00:07:29,530 --> 00:07:31,940
没错 长官 并不只有我们
No, sir. We're not alone.

103
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,190
请讲 总统先生
Go ahead, Mr. President.

104
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:37,870
你们好 尼尔和巴兹 我正在给你们打电话
Hello, Neil and Buzz. I'm talking to you by telephone

105
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:40,540
来自白宫椭圆形办公室
from the Oval Room at the White House.

106
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:45,570
这绝对是一段将要载入史册的通话
And this certainly has to be the most historic telephone call ever made.

107
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:50,790
我难以表达对你们的自豪之情
I just can't tell you how proud we all are of you.

108
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:54,880
对每一位美国人 这都是此生中最为骄傲的一天
For every American, this has to be the proudest day of our lives.

109
00:07:55,890 --> 00:07:57,920
因为你们的伟大壮举…
Because of what you have done...

110
00:07:58,010 --> 00:07:59,600
我们已降落在海面上
We have splashdown.

111
00:07:59,890 --> 00:08:02,260
太空成为了
the heavens have become a part

112
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:03,930
人类世界的一部分
of man 's world.

113
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,310
这宝贵的一刻
For one priceless moment

114
00:08:08,690 --> 00:08:10,310
将会永远铭载人类史册
in the whole history of man

115
00:08:12,030 --> 00:08:15,400
全世界的人们此刻心连心
all the people on this Earth are truly one.

116
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:20,030
为你们的壮举而感到骄傲
One in their pride in what you have done.

117
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:24,620
这鼓舞着我们要加倍努力
It inspires us to redouble our efforts

118
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:28,290
维护地球的和平与安宁
to bring peace and tranquility to Earth.

119
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:52,440
变  形  金  刚 月黑之时

120
00:09:02,870 --> 00:09:05,360
我的英雄该醒醒啦
My hero needs to wake up.

121
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:20,750
那是什么？
What is that?

122
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:23,930
是你的新幸运兔
This is your new lucky bunny.

123
00:09:28,230 --> 00:09:29,390
嗯 这是个美好的愿望 卡莉
It's a beautiful thought, Carly,

124
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,850
不过并不是兔子全身都带着好运
but I don't think it's the whole bunny that's lucky.

125
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:33,730
只有这一块地方
You see, it's just this section here.

126
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:36,390
只有兔脚这里才会带来好运
You see, it's just the rabbit foot that's lucky.

127
00:09:38,070 --> 00:09:40,400
好吧 这只是个开运魔法
Well, it's just a good luck charm.

128
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,300
能让你积极向上起来
To help you think positive?

129
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,400
今天很重要
Today's important.

130
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,780
快点 起床吧
Come on, get up.

131
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:49,990
- 嘿 系那条领带比较帅 - 好
- Hey, wear that nice tie. - Yeah.

132
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:52,160
要我留午饭钱吗？
You need any money for lunch?

133
00:09:53,670 --> 00:09:55,510
不 不用留午饭钱了
No, I don't need any money for lunch.

134
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:57,180
昨天的午饭钱还有点呢
I have money from yesterday's lunch.

135
00:09:58,010 --> 00:09:59,200
你喜欢这样是吗？
You love it, don't you?

136
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:00,880
我是你包养的玩偶
I'm just your American boy toy.

137
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:03,420
是情人兼玩偶
A lover boy toy.

138
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,430
你知道这有多郁闷吗？ 我两次拯救世界
You know how demoralizing it is to have saved the world twice

139
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,760
居然还得低声下气地去找工作
and still be groveling for a job?

140
00:10:06,850 --> 00:10:09,090
公众可不知道你拯救过世界 山姆
People don't know you saved the world, Sam.

141
00:10:09,190 --> 00:10:10,970
但我知道 我相信你
I mean, I do. I believe you.

142
00:10:11,060 --> 00:10:11,500
政府既然知情
The government knows.

143
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:14,100
就应该在华盛顿这里给我找份差事
I mean, they could hook me up with a job right here in D.C.

144
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:15,700
我应该去跟汽车人共事
I mean, I should be working with the Autobots,

145
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,930
否则就太不公平了
otherwise it's not fair.

146
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:19,110
拜托 他们已经供你上了大学
Come on, they paid for your college.

147
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,180
总统还给你颁发了英雄勋章呢
The President gave you a hero medal.

148
00:10:22,950 --> 00:10:24,280
谢谢你 山姆 干得好
Thank you, man. Great job.

149
00:10:27,290 --> 00:10:28,990
这可太酷了
That's the coolest thing that ever happened to me.

150
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,290
好吧 伙计们
All right, guys.

151
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:33,120
搞什么！
What the fuck!

152
00:10:33,210 --> 00:10:36,700
我记得 那天好像也不是你最风光的时候
And, as I recall, that wasn't even the highlight of your day.

153
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:39,500
大使先生 请
Mr. Ambassador, here.

154
00:10:39,630 --> 00:10:40,750
英国大使馆 你们是下一个
British Embassy, you're up next.

155
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,760
把它放进去 别动 看看都不行吗？
No, you don't wear it. See, you've gotta... The box.

156
00:10:49,850 --> 00:10:50,970
放进盒子 我就是想戴戴
I couldn't, even if I wanted to.

157
00:10:51,060 --> 00:10:52,680
把它放进盒子 好吗？
You're supposed to leave it in the box, right?

158
00:10:52,770 --> 00:10:54,980
放进去别动 瞧这盒子真漂亮
You keep it in this. What a gorgeous box.

159
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:04,600
对 是我的勋章
Oh, yeah. My medal.

160
00:11:04,610 --> 00:11:05,910
知道是谁给我的吗？
You know who gave that to me?

161
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:08,240
- 谁？ - POUTS
- Who? - POUTS.

162
00:11:10,210 --> 00:11:11,490
美国总统
President of the United States.

163
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:17,210
宝贝 不是每个人都能找到工作的
Babe, it's hard for everybody to get a job.

164
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,410
我没有时间了 我爸妈下星期就要来这里了
I don't have time. You see, my parents are gonna be here in a week

165
00:11:19,510 --> 00:11:21,590
他们开着房车在环游世界
on their road trip Partybus World Tour.

166
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,840
我爸来了之后 要是看到我没工作
If my dad gets here and I don't have a job,

167
00:11:24,260 --> 00:11:26,590
肯定会赏我耳光的 我得行动了
he's gonna spank me. You know, it's go time for me.

168
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:28,800
那好吧 今晚我给你安排个工作
All right, tonight, I'll give you a job.

169
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,600
给我做一顿美妙的浪漫大餐
Romance me with a nice dinner

170
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,940
然后我再多给你一点小费
and maybe you can get that bonus.

171
00:11:38,820 --> 00:11:40,400
- 真走运 - 把他弄出去
- Get lucky. - Get him out of here.

172
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:42,610
等等 不 不 不 不
Wait. No, no, no, no.

173
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:45,980
- 哦 他可真无礼！ - 她还不错
- Oh, he's gross! - She's good.

174
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,860
他们流落到了这里 得有人照顾他们
They're stranded here. Somebody's got to watch out for them.

175
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:50,280
昨天它还钻进了我的内衣抽屉
Yesterday, that one was in my underwear drawer.

176
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:52,450
研究一下嘛 顺便大饱眼福
Did research. Looking real good, too.

177
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,080
你还真打我啊！
No need to hit me.

178
00:11:54,170 --> 00:11:55,660
你可不是个普通男朋友
You are not a normal boyfriend.

179
00:11:55,660 --> 00:11:57,160
你爱的就是我这点
That's what you love about me.

180
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:59,370
- 小抱怨鬼 - 我还没说过爱这个字吧
- Crybaby. - We're not at the love word yet.

181
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:02,380
等你有能力分摊房租再说吧
Maybe a little bit closer when you're covering your half of the rent.

182
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:04,290
再见
Good-bye.

183
00:12:04,930 --> 00:12:07,290
一下雨就害得我短路！
Frickin' shorting my circuits out here!

184
00:12:07,390 --> 00:12:10,850
太没有人情味了！让我们住在小盒子里
It's inhumane, what it is! Make us live in a box

185
00:12:10,930 --> 00:12:14,220
和阳台上的那畜生待在一块！把我当成动物看待！
on a balcony, right next to a beast! Like a common animal!

186
00:12:14,310 --> 00:12:15,390
闭嘴 行吗？
Stop, okay?

187
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:17,890
你和你那丑哥们 未经允许不能进来
You and your creepy sidekick can't be in here without permission.

188
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:19,850
谁定的规矩？那个金发妞吗？
According to who? Miss Blondie Blonde?

189
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:21,810
起来 小狗狗！
Giddyup, little doggie!

190
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:27,110
- 嘿 聪明鬼 你怎么样啊？ - 还不错
- Yo, Brains, wassup?    - Doing good.

191
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,700
没意思 这集我看过了
Shit, I seen this one.

192
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:30,570
是斯巴克发疯的那集
It's the one where Spock goes nuts.

193
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,820
山姆 我真不知道该怎么跟那妞相处
You know, Sam, I don't know about moving in with this chick.

194
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,780
她要是像上一任那样甩了咱们可怎么办？
What if she dumps us like the last girl?

195
00:12:36,330 --> 00:12:37,920
她凶巴巴的 我不喜欢她
She was mean. Didn't like her.

196
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,540
咱们现在可得同仇敌忾
Us guys got to stick together.

197
00:12:40,210 --> 00:12:42,170
我们是一家人吶
We are family

198
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:44,300
我们是一家人
We are family

199
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:47,090
不 我们可不是一家人 你不过是外星难民
No, we are not family. You're a political refugee,

200
00:12:47,180 --> 00:12:49,460
我好不容易才找了一个欣赏我的人
and I have finally found someone who appreciates me for me.

201
00:12:50,010 --> 00:12:51,550
那你得告诉她 我们不是你的宠物
Well, you tell her that we're not your pets,

202
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:52,930
更不是你的玩具！
and we're not your toys!

203
00:12:53,020 --> 00:12:55,330
好吧 我们是高等的天才外星种族
All right? We're an advanced, genius alien race

204
00:12:55,420 --> 00:12:56,490
只想找个家
just looking for a home.

205
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:01,060
- 也许这不是个好主意 - 我觉得不该停
- Maybe it wasn't such a good idea. - Didn't have to stop.

206
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:02,730
拜托 他们还能怎样？ 拖走吗？
Come on. What're they going to do, tow it?

207
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:04,350
他在哪？
Where is he?

208
00:13:05,030 --> 00:13:06,360
小山山！
Sammy!

209
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:10,360
- 别这样 这很搞笑！ - 山姆
- Come on, that's funny! - Sam.

210
00:13:10,950 --> 00:13:12,610
我想死你们了
I missed you guys so much.

211
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:14,540
不想才怪呢 你觉得这身如何？
Sure, you did. What do you think?

212
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:15,860
- 瞧你们 - 可爱吧
- Look at that. - Cute.

213
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,410
- 看着很老 - 闭嘴
- You look old. - Stop it.

214
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:18,580
能看得出岁数来
Feel like I can see the end.

215
00:13:18,670 --> 00:13:20,750
我喜欢你的小领带 我的准儿媳妇在哪？
I love your little tie. Hey, where's my girl?

216
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:22,450
- 我们漂亮的卡莉哪去了？ - 她上班去了 妈妈
- Where's my beautiful Carly? - She's at work, Ma.

217
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:23,500
她找了份新工作
She's got a new job.

218
00:13:23,580 --> 00:13:24,740
我以为你们一周之后才来的
You guys said you were gonna be here in a week.

219
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:26,210
是21号 而不是11号 爹 记得吗？
The 21st, not the 11th, Dad, remember?

220
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:27,630
我们快马加鞭赶过来的
We just hauled ass in this thing.

221
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:30,550
- 一直跑到没油了 - 这大家伙跑得飞快
- We stopped for gas. - This thing. The love tub, it flies.

222
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:34,560
我们打扰你了没？比如说你的工作？
Are we keeping you from something? Like, say, your job?

223
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:36,970
嗯 上班时间到了 应该很着急吧
Well, it's about time. You had us worried.

224
00:13:39,190 --> 00:13:41,220
我有几个面试要去
I have job interviews.

225
00:13:43,230 --> 00:13:44,440
很好啊
That's good.

226
00:13:44,780 --> 00:13:45,980
- 真糟糕 - 别说了
- That sucks. - Stop it.

227
00:13:46,070 --> 00:13:47,980
别这么消极嘛 爸爸 这可是在华盛顿啊
You don't have to be so negative, Dad. You know, you're in D.C.

228
00:13:48,070 --> 00:13:49,310
咱们一家人好不容易团聚了
You're here with your son and your family.

229
00:13:49,410 --> 00:13:51,360
- 应该是高兴的时候 - 糟糕的是你居然没工作
- I mean, it's a good time. - It sucks that you don't have a job.

230
00:13:51,450 --> 00:13:53,160
就是 有很多事可以做啊 对吧？
Yeah, but there's good things to do here, too, right?

231
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,980
对嘛？逛逛博物馆和纪念碑 好吗？
Right? Museums and monuments, okay?

232
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,620
- 晚上再见 - 我要把礼物收回
- I'll see you tonight. - I'm bagging the gift.

233
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:59,500
山姆 面试应该穿正式点的裤子
Sam, I think for an interview you should wear real pants.

234
00:13:59,580 --> 00:14:01,830
你们应该天天都穿正式点的裤子
I think for life, you should wear real pants.

235
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:04,290
大黄蜂这是怎么了？
What happened to Bumblebee?

236
00:14:04,380 --> 00:14:06,500
他去执行任务了 我只好拿这个当替补
He's off on his missions. I had to get this for backup.

237
00:14:06,590 --> 00:14:09,300
- 连你的车也有工作 嗯？ - 别说了
- Your car has a job, huh? - Stop.

238
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:11,170
它能变成什么？
What does it change into?

239
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:13,300
什么也不会变 这就是件古董 妈
It doesn't change into anything. It's a collector's item, Ma.

240
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:14,050
便宜得很
I got it for a steal.

241
00:14:14,090 --> 00:14:15,430
只需要保养一下就好 相信我
It just needs some work. Trust me.

242
00:14:15,430 --> 00:14:18,140
不 这车挺可爱的 让我想起了大黄蜂
No, I think it's darling. It reminds me a lot of Bumblebee,

243
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:21,260
要是大黄蜂报废了大概就这个样子
if Bumblebee were a sad piece of shit.

244
00:14:24,190 --> 00:14:26,270
来吧 我们送你去！
Come on, we'll give you a ride!

245
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:31,020
自从我们到来之后 我们的新家 地球
In the years since our arrival, our new home, Earth,

246
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:33,230
发生了许多变化
has seen much change.

247
00:14:33,490 --> 00:14:36,410
能量检测仪保卫着每个城市
Energon detectors guard its cities now.

248
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:40,200
远程防御系统随时护卫领空
Long-range defense systems watch the skies.

249
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:43,900
<b>非法核设施 中东</b>

250
00:14:42,380 --> 00:14:46,500
所以现在我们也协助盟友们解决人类间的冲突
So now we assist our allies in solving human conflicts,

251
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:50,960
阻止人类彼此伤害
to prevent mankind from bringing harm to itself.

252
00:14:55,830 --> 00:14:57,730
是国防部长的车
The Defense Minister's car.

253
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,670
（立即放行！）

254
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:12,690
趴在地上 不许动！老实待着！
On the ground, per favore! And stay there!

255
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:32,170
我们组成秘密分队在全球各地执行各种任务
We work in secret teams on various missions around the globe.

256
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:34,710
并且与此同时
And all the while

257
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:38,800
我们也在寻找宿敌卷土重来的蛛丝马迹
we search for signs of our true enemies' return.

258
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:45,640
我是沃斯霍德 乌克兰能源部法律顾问
I am Voshkod, General Counsel with Ukrainian Department of Energy.

259
00:15:45,730 --> 00:15:47,600
我国政府会否认
My government will officially deny

260
00:15:47,690 --> 00:15:49,680
我们之间存在这次谈话
that we're having this conversation.

261
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:53,240
我们在一座废弃的核设施内有了意外发现
At one of our decommissioned facilities, a discovery was made,

262
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:56,780
恐怕是外星生物的痕迹
which I fear may be alien in nature.

263
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,610
那座核设施的名字叫 切尔诺贝利
The facility's name is Chernobyl.

264
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:10,980
<b>切尔诺贝利核电站废墟</b>

265
00:16:21,020 --> 00:16:22,380
沃斯霍德先生
Mr. Voshkod.

266
00:16:23,270 --> 00:16:25,310
自1986年起这里就成了一座空城
So, uninhabited since '86.

267
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:28,890
我听说两万年之内都不适宜人类居住？
I hear it won't be livable again for another 20,000 years?

268
00:16:29,150 --> 00:16:32,310
至少两万年 乌克兰原本土壤肥沃
At least. Ukraine was the most fertile land.

269
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,690
那真是场悲剧
It's a tragedy.

270
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:35,190
这边请
This way.

271
00:16:35,990 --> 00:16:38,700
做好准备！我们只能待60分钟
Gear up! We have 60 minutes on the ground.

272
00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:40,820
注意各自的辐射量水平
Watch your radiation levels.

273
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:46,450
沃斯霍德先生 你的防护衣呢？
Mr. Voshkod, where's your protective gear?

274
00:16:52,050 --> 00:16:54,330
你的防护衣在哪？
Where's your protective gear?

275
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:55,510
已经没必要了
It would not matter.

276
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:58,340
对我来说 死是迟早的事
For me, it's only a matter of time.

277
00:16:58,430 --> 00:16:59,710
穿过这所学校
Through the school.

278
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:04,680
尤里会带你们下去 另外还有件事 上校
Yuri will take you below. And one other thing, Colonel.

279
00:17:04,770 --> 00:17:07,680
别说出去 这里进行过能源实验
In private, there were some energy experiments.

280
00:17:10,650 --> 00:17:12,060
待会儿再说
It can wait.

281
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:25,660
继续前进 跟紧点
Keep moving. Stay tight.

282
00:17:29,130 --> 00:17:31,870
好 就是这里 我想是找到了
Okay, right here. I think I found it.

283
00:17:33,130 --> 00:17:35,120
指挥官 我们有画面了
Optimus, we got a visual.

284
00:17:37,130 --> 00:17:41,130
我们发现了一个东西被金属器械夹住了
Looks like the object's clamped in some kind of a metal harness.

285
00:17:42,850 --> 00:17:45,210
这是什么？伙计们！
What's this? Guys!

286
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,850
这上面怎么有苏联太空竞赛计划的标志？
Why does this thing have Soviet space program markings on it?

287
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,390
史普尼克？（苏联发射的全球第一颗人造卫星）
Sputnik?

288
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:52,000
有能量读数 长官
Energon readings, sir.

289
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,100
非常强烈
It's strong.

290
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,650
在我们下面 来得很快
Below us. It's coming fast.

291
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:05,440
过来了 过来了！
Contact, contact!

292
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:21,500
到上面去！快走 快 快！
Get topside now! Move, move, move!

293
00:18:48,290 --> 00:18:51,330
- 快走 快走！ - 准备！重武器准备！
- Let's go! - Weapons up! Heavy weapons up!

294
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:53,160
躲在我身后！
Stay behind me!

295
00:18:55,460 --> 00:18:56,670
擎天柱！
Optimus!

296
00:19:02,390 --> 00:19:03,380
快撤！
Fall back!

297
00:19:04,390 --> 00:19:05,880
它绕着我们打转！
It's circling around us!

298
00:19:06,390 --> 00:19:07,720
它在接近我们侧翼！
It's taking our flank!

299
00:19:14,070 --> 00:19:15,150
准备重武器！
Get the heavy weapon!

300
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:19,310
擎天柱！
Optimus!

301
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:37,040
那是什么鬼东西？
What the hell was that thing?

302
00:19:38,090 --> 00:19:39,420
那个
That

303
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,540
是震荡波
is Shockwave.

304
00:19:43,090 --> 00:19:44,930
他怎么想要这个？
Why was he after this?

305
00:19:46,100 --> 00:19:47,340
这不可能
It's impossible.

306
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:50,090
这是个引擎零件
This is an engine part

307
00:19:50,180 --> 00:19:53,320
来自一艘失踪已久的汽车人飞船
from a long lost Autobot ship.

308
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,740
与你合作很愉快
Pleasure working with you.

309
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:24,540
要去面试了 真让人兴奋
Interviews. This is so exciting.

310
00:20:24,970 --> 00:20:26,460
甜心 你要口香糖吗？
Honey, do you want some gum?

311
00:20:26,550 --> 00:20:29,300
每次你一紧张 口气就很重
Your breath gets really gnarly when you're nervous.

312
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:33,100
- 维特维奇先生？ - 对 到此为止了
- Mr. Witwicky? - Yeah. Search is over.

313
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:34,980
我叫惠特利
I'm Mr. Whitley.

314
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:39,610
- 还有别人吗？ - 没有
- Is anybody else joining? - No.

315
00:20:40,150 --> 00:20:42,020
没有？你要我坐到那里？
No? You want me to move right there?

316
00:20:42,110 --> 00:20:43,150
- 我就坐到那里 - 最好别坐
- I'll move right there. - I'd prefer not.

317
00:20:44,530 --> 00:20:46,190
好了吗？开始吧
Ready? Begin.

318
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:48,690
我是应届毕业生 主修地缘政治学 辅修文学专业
Graduated this year. Majored in geopolitics. Minor in tech studies.

319
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:50,190
兴趣在于政府与科技之间的
Very interested in government and technology,

320
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:51,620
如何进行对接和并存
how that's gonna intersect and co-exist.

321
00:20:51,700 --> 00:20:52,910
要塑造未来
Shape the future.

322
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,910
当初干嘛要费劲地送他去读常春藤盟校？
Why did we bother sending him to an lvy college for?

323
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,240
都毕业三个月了还找不到工作？
Three months out of school and he can't find a job?

324
00:20:58,340 --> 00:20:59,830
松笨先生…
Mr. Masuhisu...

325
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:01,080
我叫松本
Matsumoto.

326
00:21:01,170 --> 00:21:02,710
- 松本 - 松笨
- Matsumoto. - Moto.

327
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:04,580
- 玛莎 可以叫你玛莎吗？ - 不 不可以
- Martha, can I call you Martha? - No, you may not.

328
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,590
好了 杰克 这世上有两种人
Okay, Jack, there's two types of people in this world.

329
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:09,010
一种是思想家 一种是实干家
There's think ers, there's doers.

330
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:13,260
一种是胜利者 一种是梦想者 还有一种是好哥们
There's winners, there's dreamers, and there's buddies.

331
00:21:13,350 --> 00:21:15,340
谈谈你的缺点吧？
What about some weaknesses?

332
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:17,220
我没有…
I don't...

333
00:21:17,310 --> 00:21:18,520
您长得很亲切
You have a very trustworthy face.

334
00:21:18,610 --> 00:21:21,020
让我想起亚洲版的桑德斯上校（肯德基的创始人）
You remind me of like an Asian Colonel Sanders.

335
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,600
很值得我信任
A man I can trust.

336
00:21:22,690 --> 00:21:23,650
他是00后
He's a millennial.

337
00:21:23,740 --> 00:21:26,230
是说他们是 你懂的 迷惘的一代
That means they're the, you know, like lost generation.

338
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:28,150
联邦调查局为什么找你？
Why was the FBI looking for you?

339
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:30,150
为「什么」？
The what?

340
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:31,610
呃 联邦调查局 你正好提起那事了
Yeah, FBI. Good of you to flag that.

341
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:34,790
在你十四岁时应该干过外星人那种狂热的事
It was during all that alien craziness when you were 14.

